WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.458
♪ La-la-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪

00:08.541 --> 00:09.916
-[grunts]
-Mmm.

00:12.416 --> 00:15.416
Who has an amazing herd?
I have an amazing herd.

00:15.500 --> 00:17.625
Who said so? Waterbaby!

00:17.708 --> 00:19.958
Funny she didn't mention
where the next Shaman is.

00:20.041 --> 00:22.958
I know where all the Shamans are,
for the most part.

00:23.041 --> 00:26.291
And your sass mouth
will appreciate that the next Shaman

00:26.375 --> 00:28.291
is right over this hill in the--

00:28.375 --> 00:30.375
[eerie music playing]

00:36.125 --> 00:39.250
[Glendale] Um, Wammawink? Wammawink?

00:40.041 --> 00:41.500
Hmm? Oh!

00:41.583 --> 00:44.500
Wait. Why am I walking this way?
Just let me just…

00:45.041 --> 00:46.541
[whimsical music playing]

00:47.250 --> 00:48.291
That's weird.

00:50.791 --> 00:55.125
You were saying something about
my sass mouth needing to head that way.

00:55.208 --> 00:56.208
Right.

00:56.291 --> 01:01.125
The first stop is the Fraternal Twin
Tree Shamans of the Lost Forest!

01:01.208 --> 01:04.583
Hold on, hold on, hold on.
How far we gotta go into there?

01:04.666 --> 01:06.958
It's getting dark,
and Durpleton hates the dark.

01:07.041 --> 01:09.166
Ched, you hate it more than I do.

01:09.250 --> 01:10.958
The other day, you cried.

01:11.041 --> 01:13.125
Maybe we should just camp out here.

01:13.208 --> 01:15.666
Zulius's already doing his night routine.

01:15.750 --> 01:19.083
[Zulius over recording]
You've got the bod and the 'tude.

01:19.166 --> 01:21.708
Sweat is just nature's glitter.

01:21.791 --> 01:24.833
It makes you shine
even more than you already do.

01:24.916 --> 01:25.916
Mm-hmm.

01:26.000 --> 01:28.333
Okay. Well, I'm not afraid of the dark,

01:28.416 --> 01:31.833
so tell me what these Tree Shamans
look like, I'll find them on my own.

01:31.916 --> 01:35.291
Oh. Oh, sure. Sure.
You know, they're trees.

01:36.375 --> 01:38.125
Trees in a forest. Great.

01:38.208 --> 01:40.458
Any distinguishing features
I should be aware of?

01:40.541 --> 01:42.333
They run around like Gebbrey?

01:42.416 --> 01:44.958
-Nobody runs around like Gebbrey.
-[gasps]

01:45.041 --> 01:45.958
So cold!

01:46.041 --> 01:47.708
[whimpers] So cold!

01:47.791 --> 01:49.750
Oh, that Gebbrey.

01:49.833 --> 01:54.083
-[Gebbrey whimpering]
-He's got some sweet, sweet gams.

01:54.166 --> 01:55.500
[sighs]

01:56.125 --> 01:57.416
[snoring]

01:57.500 --> 01:58.958
[soothing music playing]

01:59.916 --> 02:01.291
[yawning]

02:02.083 --> 02:03.875
[all snoring]

02:03.958 --> 02:06.791
This isn't gonna happen, is it?

02:07.416 --> 02:11.833
[sighs] I guess it doesn't make any sense
to go there when it's dark anyway.

02:11.916 --> 02:13.000
[grunts]

02:15.666 --> 02:16.791
[Wammawink] Psst!

02:16.875 --> 02:18.000
[softly] Baby girl.

02:19.083 --> 02:20.250
You awake?

02:20.333 --> 02:21.791
Uh… Um…

02:22.375 --> 02:23.916
Are you talkin' to me?

02:24.416 --> 02:28.041
-Yeah. Baby girl.
-Don't call me that. Call me Horse.

02:28.125 --> 02:31.708
[stuttering] Can you whisper?
I don't want them to hear.

02:33.416 --> 02:34.666
Okay, sure.

02:35.208 --> 02:37.333
-[whispers] What do you want?
-[sighs]

02:37.416 --> 02:42.041
You ever feel that thing where… where
your whole body feels completely frozen?

02:42.125 --> 02:44.208
[inhales] You're all… [babbles]

02:44.291 --> 02:45.916
Your brain feels… [babbles]

02:46.083 --> 02:48.583
And you keep,
you know, staring into space?

02:48.666 --> 02:50.000
No. Never.

02:50.458 --> 02:51.583
I think I need

02:52.666 --> 02:53.625
something.

02:54.333 --> 02:56.041
Yeah. Sleep.

02:57.083 --> 02:58.625
Yeah. Okay.

02:59.500 --> 03:01.166
[fast forwarding]

03:12.625 --> 03:14.250
[groaning]

03:14.333 --> 03:16.583
-[screams]
-[all screaming]

03:16.666 --> 03:17.666
[groans]

03:19.250 --> 03:23.000
That was a really bad rendition
of our wake-up song.

03:23.083 --> 03:25.791
No time for wake-up songs today.
We gotta go.

03:26.541 --> 03:30.166
[Wammawink] ♪ In Centaurworld ♪

03:30.250 --> 03:32.916
-[neighing]
-[vocalizing]

03:33.000 --> 03:34.125
[squeaks]

03:35.625 --> 03:38.708
♪ And that's the twelfth verse
Of the wake-up song ♪

03:38.791 --> 03:39.708
[farts]

03:39.791 --> 03:42.875
I'm sorry, Father.
Please don't be mad. [farts]

03:42.958 --> 03:44.083
[whimpers]

03:45.375 --> 03:48.208
Do we wanna try and unpack that? Or…

03:48.291 --> 03:49.458
Uh-uh.

03:49.541 --> 03:51.375
[eerie music playing]

03:51.458 --> 03:54.666
-So… are we going in or what?
-[whimpering]

03:55.875 --> 03:57.500
Uh, Wammawink?

03:58.375 --> 04:00.958
What happened?
I thought you were leading the charge.

04:01.041 --> 04:04.625
Oh! That's what I'm doing.
Charging. Leading the chars.

04:07.125 --> 04:09.208
[sighs] Come on. This is important.

04:09.291 --> 04:13.291
I need you to stop being your usual
goofy self and take me to these Shamans.

04:13.375 --> 04:15.375
[gasps] Ooh! Can I come, too?

04:15.458 --> 04:17.250
[farts, groans]

04:17.333 --> 04:19.625
That's obviously not her usual goofy self.

04:19.708 --> 04:23.458
Something is wrong. Typical horse.
I mean, sociopath much?

04:23.541 --> 04:27.916
-[huffs] This guy.
-Ched, what is your problem with horses?

04:28.000 --> 04:32.416
Horse, what's your problem with someone
having a problem with horses, Horse?

04:33.083 --> 04:35.125
She's fine, everybody. Let's go.

04:35.208 --> 04:36.833
[adventurous music playing]

04:38.083 --> 04:40.083
[eerie music playing]

04:43.583 --> 04:47.541
Okay, Wammawink. You're the Shaman expert.
Is that the Shaman?

04:48.166 --> 04:50.916
25% of shamans are right-handed.

04:51.000 --> 04:53.500
So, is that a no?

04:53.583 --> 04:56.833
Hey! What about this one?

04:56.916 --> 04:59.833
-Look at him.
-[quavers] I don't want any trouble.

04:59.916 --> 05:01.708
32% have no hands.

05:01.791 --> 05:04.125
All righty, then. No harm, no foul.

05:04.208 --> 05:06.500
I have a family!

05:06.583 --> 05:09.208
14% have three nondominant legs.

05:09.291 --> 05:11.833
100% of shamans are shamans.

05:11.916 --> 05:14.541
How many key pieces am I holding up?

05:15.541 --> 05:17.333
[Wammawink] One. [chuckles]

05:17.416 --> 05:19.958
Yes, but it needs to be six.

05:20.041 --> 05:23.583
And I'm gonna need your help
getting the other five.

05:23.666 --> 05:25.833
[chuckles] Guess I'm doin' math now.

05:25.916 --> 05:28.666
Horse, it's not always about me.

05:28.750 --> 05:31.125
-I mean, you.
-Hey, ding-dongs. Look.

05:31.208 --> 05:35.250
[eerie voices reading]

05:35.875 --> 05:38.875
There's signs!
Yes! We're in the right place.

05:38.958 --> 05:42.250
Exposition leaves.
You're in the right place.

05:42.333 --> 05:44.333
[orchestral music playing]

05:50.500 --> 05:52.500
[music builds]

05:54.833 --> 05:57.583
[clears throat] Greetings, Shaman. I…

05:57.666 --> 06:00.708
Uh, we are here for a piece of the key.

06:00.791 --> 06:03.208
Oh, not that tree. So embarrassing.

06:03.291 --> 06:06.416
[Tree Shamans] Psst.
You need to look over here.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.958
You know you want to.

06:09.041 --> 06:11.708
[clears throat] Hello, Tree Shamans.

06:11.791 --> 06:13.250
I am Horse.

06:13.333 --> 06:19.250
I have been sent by Waterbaby
to collect a piece of, um, this thing.

06:19.333 --> 06:21.958
-And I… Oh, uh, okay.
-[guitar music playing]

06:22.041 --> 06:24.041
[wind whistling]

06:24.750 --> 06:27.291
[Tree Shamans] ♪ Our roots reach down
Our branches rise ♪

06:27.375 --> 06:28.708
♪ From sky to ground ♪

06:28.791 --> 06:34.458
♪ Our wooden eyes have gazed upon
Desire, hope, and greed ♪

06:34.958 --> 06:40.166
♪ But to each soul who walks this way
A tree disclaimer we must say ♪

06:40.250 --> 06:44.583
♪ We give not what you want
But what you need ♪

06:45.208 --> 06:50.583
♪ For the greenery has always seen
The reason and the rhyme ♪

06:50.666 --> 06:55.291
♪ But we've had nothing but time
Since we've been seeds ♪

06:55.375 --> 06:58.083
♪ And you might believe
You know your truth ♪

06:58.166 --> 07:00.875
♪ But truth can oft be lies ♪

07:00.958 --> 07:05.250
♪ For you might just be surprised
By what you need ♪

07:06.166 --> 07:10.375
♪ What you need, la-la-la-la
What you need ♪

07:11.333 --> 07:15.500
♪ Oh, you might just be surprised
By what you need ♪

07:16.416 --> 07:20.583
♪ What you need, la-la-la-la
What you need ♪

07:21.750 --> 07:24.833
♪ Oh, you might just be surprised ♪

07:26.208 --> 07:30.541
♪ By what you need ♪

07:31.708 --> 07:35.625
Yeah. So, is that a yes,
you'll give us the key piece?

07:35.708 --> 07:39.625
-[big tree] Indeed. Whatever you need.
-Which might be what you want.

07:39.708 --> 07:41.666
Not seein' the difference here.

07:42.125 --> 07:43.291
[whooshing]

07:43.375 --> 07:46.000
[big tree] Step up to the altar
and find out.

07:48.250 --> 07:50.916
Ooh, hey, hey, hey.
Where you goin', buddy?

07:51.000 --> 07:52.833
I need you right over here.

07:52.916 --> 07:56.375
I need the next piece of the key
because I want to go home.

07:56.458 --> 08:01.625
But I also want the next piece
because I need to go home.

08:01.708 --> 08:02.708
What?

08:02.791 --> 08:05.583
Don't overtax your horse brain there, bub.

08:05.666 --> 08:08.958
I am a tree expert. A savant.

08:09.041 --> 08:10.791
I got this. Check it.

08:11.750 --> 08:15.041
-[Centaurs gasp]
-Um, what makes you the tree expert?

08:15.708 --> 08:19.416
Uh, what makes me a tree expert?
Oh, okay. I've lived in a tree.

08:19.500 --> 08:20.583
[scoffs] This guy.

08:20.666 --> 08:24.458
You wouldn't know a tree
if it fell on your thick horse skull.

08:24.541 --> 08:26.000
Hold the can of Cheez Whiz.

08:26.083 --> 08:29.583
How hard does this have to be?
You go up to the thing you make wishes on,

08:29.666 --> 08:32.208
and you make your wish.
Let's go. It's easy.

08:32.291 --> 08:34.291
[groans] Nothing here's that easy.

08:34.375 --> 08:38.083
There's gotta be a catch.
They were singing about wants and needs…

08:38.166 --> 08:43.083
[gasps] You guys! What if what you want
and what you need are the same thing?

08:43.166 --> 08:44.833
Like me and talking farts.

08:44.916 --> 08:47.083
Mmm, so…

08:47.166 --> 08:49.708
Wait. You want your farts to talk to you?

08:49.791 --> 08:53.625
Oh, they already do.
I just want them to be nice to me.

08:53.708 --> 08:56.125
Yeah. We-- None of us wanna hear this.

08:56.208 --> 09:01.666
♪ He never says anything nice
When I eat the foods that I love ♪

09:01.750 --> 09:03.666
♪ All he says is… ♪ [farts]

09:03.750 --> 09:05.500
♪ And… And sometimes-- ♪

09:05.583 --> 09:08.083
Not now, Durpleton. What's your deal, man?

09:08.166 --> 09:10.750
I feel like you have a problem with me
'cause I'm a horse.

09:10.833 --> 09:13.291
Well, Horse, I don't know what a horse is.

09:13.375 --> 09:16.166
I know what a horse Centaur is,
and I hate them.

09:16.250 --> 09:18.166
-They're only half horse.
-[grunts]

09:18.250 --> 09:21.041
So, by my math,
you're twice as bad as they are.

09:21.125 --> 09:23.041
-[big tree] Granted.
-[whooshing]

09:23.125 --> 09:24.791
[suspenseful music playing]

09:31.041 --> 09:33.208
-[fart] I'm proud of you.
-[Durpleton gasps]

09:33.291 --> 09:35.958
My wish came true!

09:36.041 --> 09:37.666
I'll take your word for it.

09:37.750 --> 09:41.500
All righty. Ched's turn.
Uh, let's see. We got the… [sniffs]

09:41.583 --> 09:43.541
Yeah, that's your standard bark.

09:43.625 --> 09:45.166
Yeah. Full-on barkage.

09:47.000 --> 09:48.166
That checks out.

09:48.250 --> 09:51.291
Let me show you how
to handle a wishing tree, Horse.

09:51.375 --> 09:53.791
They never mentioned wishes.

09:53.875 --> 09:56.250
Wish. Want. Need. What's the difference?

09:56.333 --> 09:58.875
-[big tree] Granted.
-Wait. What's granted?

09:58.958 --> 10:00.416
I didn't say anything.

10:01.541 --> 10:03.083
[whooshing]

10:03.166 --> 10:04.583
[rumbling]

10:07.666 --> 10:09.250
[Centaurs] Uh…

10:09.916 --> 10:11.583
-What?
-[screams, laughs]

10:12.333 --> 10:14.333
[laughing hysterically]

10:17.625 --> 10:19.083
-Sorry.
-[Ched] What?

10:19.166 --> 10:21.250
What is so haha?

10:21.958 --> 10:25.416
Wha-- Wha-- [screams]

10:25.500 --> 10:28.333
Am I… What did you do to me,
you stinkin' freaks?

10:28.416 --> 10:31.166
[screaming] Oh no!

10:31.916 --> 10:33.625
Backwards knees! [groans]

10:33.708 --> 10:36.875
What? See? This doesn't make any sense.

10:36.958 --> 10:40.291
Do you really think Ched
secretly wanted to be a horse?

10:40.958 --> 10:41.958
I can't believe.

10:42.041 --> 10:44.916
No. I… I mean, look at that.

10:45.000 --> 10:47.500
[groans, yells]

10:48.125 --> 10:52.083
Fight me, you cowards. Come on!
Bring it on! Fight me! [sobs]

10:52.166 --> 10:58.333
Unless Ched needed to become a horse
because he hates horses so much.

10:58.416 --> 11:00.000
You did this, Horse.

11:00.083 --> 11:03.958
This was your wish, wasn't it?
Yeah. You cut me in the wish line.

11:04.041 --> 11:06.041
My gosh. Can you shut up for a sec?

11:06.125 --> 11:07.875
This is how you reproduce, isn't it?

11:07.958 --> 11:11.791
I think I get it, but I can't risk
messing this up, so we better test it.

11:11.875 --> 11:13.166
Zulius, you go next.

11:13.250 --> 11:15.541
Ha! I don't need a thing.

11:15.625 --> 11:18.541
[chuckles] You can't improve
on perfection.

11:19.083 --> 11:24.208
Mmm, well, I want Wammawink
to snap out of whatever, uh…

11:25.333 --> 11:27.166
whatever all this is.

11:27.250 --> 11:31.666
But I probably also need to stop stealing.

11:31.750 --> 11:34.833
-Oh, floating, like on a cloud.
-Ah, let's do a spin.

11:34.958 --> 11:36.208
[screaming]

11:36.291 --> 11:38.666
There's no way I'm giving all that up.

11:38.750 --> 11:40.291
I feel like I'm on a boat.

11:41.083 --> 11:45.083
Come on. A, B, C, D. No, no! Okay.

11:45.166 --> 11:47.375
If there's really something wrong
with Wammawink,

11:47.458 --> 11:50.791
then the trees should fix her
because she needs to get better.

11:50.875 --> 11:53.083
[Ched] First two are one,
back two are two.

11:53.166 --> 11:54.916
No, doesn't work! How do you do it?

11:55.000 --> 11:58.250
Well, it cured me
of my cruel and unusual farts.

11:59.625 --> 12:00.625
[bell dings]

12:00.708 --> 12:01.958
So I say do it.

12:05.500 --> 12:06.625
[big tree] Granted.

12:08.625 --> 12:09.875
[whooshing]

12:09.958 --> 12:10.958
[snoring]

12:12.083 --> 12:13.666
[moaning]

12:15.166 --> 12:16.416
[snoring]

12:21.333 --> 12:23.750
Aha! She needed sleep!

12:24.375 --> 12:26.916
I need the next piece
of the key to go home.

12:27.000 --> 12:29.416
-[big tree] Granted.
-[whooshing]

12:31.208 --> 12:36.000
Oh, you stupid trees!
That's what I needed, for her to get lost.

12:36.083 --> 12:40.083
-Why'd you have to horse me up like this?
-Wait. Is she gone forever?

12:40.166 --> 12:44.208
[fart] Oh, baby boy,
that is what she said she wanted.

12:44.291 --> 12:45.625
Yeah, you're right.

12:45.708 --> 12:47.375
[suspenseful music playing]

12:52.416 --> 12:53.416
Wait a minute.

12:53.500 --> 12:56.875
[sniffing] Death? Fire?

12:56.958 --> 12:59.166
[sniffing] Hopelessness?

12:59.250 --> 13:02.750
[gasps] Home!
They sent me straight back home!

13:02.833 --> 13:04.958
Rider! Rider!

13:05.041 --> 13:06.666
Oh. I can still talk.

13:06.750 --> 13:08.333
[sighs] Rider!

13:11.166 --> 13:14.250
Looks like we'll be
stuck here a while, so…

13:14.916 --> 13:17.500
The fart thing. What is that about?

13:18.083 --> 13:21.416
[whimpering] Yeah,
tell us more about your mean butt

13:21.500 --> 13:24.125
-before I have a panic attack.
-[farts]

13:25.625 --> 13:31.791
♪ He never said anything nice
When I'd eat the foods that I love ♪

13:31.875 --> 13:33.875
♪ All he said was… ♪ [farts]

13:33.958 --> 13:35.458
♪ And… And sometimes… ♪

13:35.541 --> 13:36.791
[farting]

13:38.375 --> 13:44.041
♪ But now that he can say
Something sweet ♪

13:44.125 --> 13:49.958
♪ I know that he will compliment me ♪

13:50.041 --> 13:56.333
♪ For example, "You're the best son
And you're handsome and smart" ♪

13:56.416 --> 14:00.958
♪ Just please say
Something from the heart ♪

14:02.250 --> 14:04.500
[fart chuckling] Oh, my sweet boy.

14:05.375 --> 14:07.083
Hee-haw!

14:07.166 --> 14:08.375
Argh!

14:10.458 --> 14:11.583
Rider!

14:11.666 --> 14:12.875
[pants]

14:12.958 --> 14:14.750
[suspenseful music playing]

14:15.375 --> 14:16.625
This doesn't look…

14:17.333 --> 14:18.750
[buzzing]

14:19.375 --> 14:23.333
[screams] I'm still stuck in Centaurworld!

14:23.416 --> 14:25.583
[chittering]

14:25.666 --> 14:27.583
Ugh! Hello?

14:27.666 --> 14:29.791
-Anybody out there?
-[sobbing]

14:32.375 --> 14:33.916
[gasps] Wammawink!

14:34.000 --> 14:37.416
Whoa, you're tiny.
Did the trees turn you back into a baby?

14:37.500 --> 14:38.875
[sobbing]

14:40.333 --> 14:42.333
[sniffling]

14:43.000 --> 14:44.791
Hmm, Wammawink?

14:44.875 --> 14:46.541
Are… Are you okay?

14:47.166 --> 14:48.750
[sniffling]

14:48.833 --> 14:50.666
[wind whooshing]

14:53.458 --> 14:54.458
[sniffling]

14:55.708 --> 14:59.250
It's just a bad dream.
When I wake up, they'll all be back.

14:59.333 --> 15:02.791
It's just a bad dream.
When I wake up, they'll all be back.

15:02.875 --> 15:06.541
It's just a bad dream.
When I wake up, they'll all be back.

15:07.125 --> 15:10.125
Are you… Are you ignoring me
or am I invisible?

15:13.250 --> 15:14.541
Invisible. Got it.

15:15.500 --> 15:16.500
[Wammawink] Hi.

15:17.791 --> 15:20.333
Looks like you
and I are the only survivors.

15:20.958 --> 15:23.583
Well, as long as we have each other, we--

15:24.875 --> 15:26.083
Oh.

15:26.666 --> 15:28.666
[sniffling]

15:28.750 --> 15:30.750
[somber music playing]

15:32.333 --> 15:35.291
Oh, Tree Shamans,
can you bring my herd back?

15:35.375 --> 15:38.708
Oh. The Lost Forest was your village.

15:39.416 --> 15:42.000
Please? Please?

15:44.708 --> 15:47.125
[big tree] We know this is what you want.

15:47.958 --> 15:50.333
[little tree] But this is not
what you need.

15:50.875 --> 15:53.291
-[sobbing]
-What?

15:54.000 --> 15:56.958
Thanks for sharing
your shade with our village.

15:57.041 --> 15:59.333
I'm gonna go find somewhere else to stay.

15:59.416 --> 16:01.291
[sobbing]

16:05.166 --> 16:09.000
Are you kidding? She was suffering,
and you could have helped her.

16:09.083 --> 16:10.875
Why would you just ignore her?

16:10.958 --> 16:13.083
She's selfless and kind.

16:13.166 --> 16:18.041
She barely knows me, and she brought me
to the place where she lost everything.

16:18.125 --> 16:21.875
But she came here anyway because
she doesn't want me to hurt this much.

16:21.958 --> 16:26.208
If you won't bring back her village,
the least you could do is comfort her.

16:27.500 --> 16:31.583
Don't think we're done here.
You haven't seen the last of me. [snorts]

16:38.333 --> 16:40.708
Uh, Wammawink? [chuckles]

16:41.625 --> 16:43.708
I know you can't hear me, but…

16:47.291 --> 16:48.333
It gets better.

16:49.166 --> 16:53.833
You grow up and you meet
some really wacky Centaurs who sing

16:53.916 --> 16:57.458
and laugh
and do all kinds of goofball stuff.

16:57.541 --> 17:00.875
And they love you and you love them. And…

17:00.958 --> 17:06.958
[sighs] I wish I could say this to you
and you could actually hear me.

17:07.541 --> 17:09.000
[Wammawink sniffling]

17:11.083 --> 17:13.083
♪ You're okay ♪

17:15.875 --> 17:18.583
♪ You're all right ♪

17:20.416 --> 17:27.125
♪ I'll never ever leave your side ♪

17:28.375 --> 17:31.375
♪ I will stay ♪

17:32.666 --> 17:35.375
♪ And I will fight ♪

17:37.125 --> 17:42.333
♪ With you ♪

17:44.875 --> 17:47.458
[whooshing]

17:48.416 --> 17:49.625
[wind whooshing]

17:49.708 --> 17:51.291
[snoring]

17:52.958 --> 17:55.041
[gasps] Huh?

17:55.125 --> 17:56.500
[solemn music playing]

17:57.375 --> 17:59.500
-[snorts]
-You're back!

17:59.583 --> 18:01.583
[both gasp, scream]

18:01.666 --> 18:03.291
Oh, we're hugging you.

18:03.375 --> 18:06.250
Yep. I had some unfinished business.

18:09.083 --> 18:10.625
[Zulius] Oh.

18:10.708 --> 18:13.625
-Ched! Horse came back to fight you.
-[bell dings]

18:15.375 --> 18:17.166
Well, I hate that you're back,

18:17.250 --> 18:21.666
but I'm glad there's another horse
to hate besides myself.

18:21.750 --> 18:24.750
If you don't like me, fine.
But you like her, right?

18:24.833 --> 18:28.416
Who? Wammawink? She's all right.
Thousand times better than you.

18:28.500 --> 18:30.625
-Get up.
-Are we gonna--

18:30.708 --> 18:33.958
We seriously gonna fight?
Is this what we're gonna do?

18:34.041 --> 18:37.375
[scoffs] No. You're a horse now,
so you have to learn to kick.

18:39.166 --> 18:40.250
Oh.

18:40.333 --> 18:42.375
Told you I'd be back. [grunts]

18:42.458 --> 18:43.458
See?

18:44.375 --> 18:47.083
-[big tree] Whoa, whoa! Calm down!
-Like this.

18:47.166 --> 18:49.625
-[grunting]
-[big tree] Whoa, whoa, whoa.

18:49.708 --> 18:51.083
Wammawink, wake up.

18:51.166 --> 18:52.833
Horse… Horse is losin' it!

18:54.416 --> 18:57.416
[fart] You are handling this crisis
really well!

18:57.500 --> 18:58.833
Aw, thanks, Dada.

18:58.916 --> 19:02.791
Uh, Horse, I don't think
they're gonna give you the key piece

19:02.875 --> 19:04.375
if you keep doing that.

19:04.458 --> 19:07.458
Watch me, Ched. Forward and back!

19:07.541 --> 19:09.333
[big tree] We're just trees.

19:09.416 --> 19:10.291
Okay.

19:10.375 --> 19:12.458
Frontways, and… ba-blam!

19:12.541 --> 19:13.750
That'll teach ya.

19:17.541 --> 19:18.916
It's beautiful.

19:19.000 --> 19:22.208
They're bonding over
their shared hatred of trees.

19:22.291 --> 19:25.208
-[Horse] I'll give you what you need.
-[creaking]

19:28.541 --> 19:31.333
-[big tree] Uh-oh, going down!
-[snorts] Uh-oh.

19:31.416 --> 19:32.708
[thuds]

19:34.916 --> 19:36.666
-[whimpering]
-She killed it!

19:36.750 --> 19:38.625
Oh, you really done it now.

19:39.208 --> 19:40.375
What did we do?

19:40.458 --> 19:42.083
[Ched grunting]

19:42.166 --> 19:44.125
Ched, you're not a horse anymore.

19:44.208 --> 19:45.583
[grunts, gasps]

19:46.291 --> 19:48.500
Yes! Yes!

19:48.583 --> 19:51.791
I'm back, baby! Uh, ba-blam!

19:51.875 --> 19:54.458
[yawning]

19:54.541 --> 19:57.041
-What's going…
-[squeals excitedly]

19:57.125 --> 20:00.166
-I missed you so much!
-Oh, I can't breathe.

20:00.250 --> 20:02.125
What happened?

20:02.666 --> 20:04.333
Oh, okay. Hi.

20:04.833 --> 20:07.666
Mmm, I'm sorry I wasn't there for you.

20:07.750 --> 20:09.583
[sighs] I didn't know.

20:09.666 --> 20:14.125
I can't believe you would come back
to this horrible forest for me.

20:14.208 --> 20:18.125
It's okay. I think I kinda needed that.

20:18.208 --> 20:19.250
[snorts]

20:20.000 --> 20:23.000
Did we get the key piece?
Mission accomplished?

20:23.666 --> 20:26.083
-What happened to the tree?
-[Horse] Well…

20:26.166 --> 20:30.666
Ched and I, we kicked… we kicked the tree.

20:30.750 --> 20:33.458
A lot. We kicked…
We kicked it a lot. And then…

20:33.541 --> 20:37.125
Oh, I got ya, baby girl.
Say no more. Say no more.

20:37.208 --> 20:41.208
I'm pickin' up what you're puttin' down.
Like what Waterbaby sang.

20:41.291 --> 20:43.041
♪ Hidden in seas… ♪

20:43.125 --> 20:44.125
[mumbling]

20:44.208 --> 20:45.958
♪ …trees! ♪

20:46.041 --> 20:47.166
Wait. No.

20:49.166 --> 20:52.958
Wow, Horse. So taking out the tree
was your plan all along.

20:53.041 --> 20:54.125
You're so smart.

20:54.208 --> 20:58.125
Uh, yeah. I definitely knew
where the key piece was the whole time.

20:58.208 --> 21:01.541
Why y'all standing around for?
Time to move on.

21:02.083 --> 21:04.458
[gasps] Oh, my brain feels lighter,

21:04.541 --> 21:07.916
but my hooves feel like
they're made of million-pound rocks.

21:08.000 --> 21:09.916
Then let me lighten your burden,

21:10.000 --> 21:11.583
baby girl.

21:13.875 --> 21:15.000
[snorts]

21:15.916 --> 21:19.458
Huh. No one has carried me
like this since I was small.

21:19.541 --> 21:22.708
-[fart] Who is my little cutie? Come here!
-Oh.

21:22.791 --> 21:25.833
It looks like I got to keep
my compliment farts.

21:26.375 --> 21:29.541
[little tree] Wait. Hang on.
We're giving stuff away now?

21:29.625 --> 21:32.416
[big tree] We gave her
what she thought she needed.

21:32.500 --> 21:35.583
But what comes next
might not be what she wants.

21:36.458 --> 21:38.291
♪ Hush now ♪

21:38.375 --> 21:40.125
♪ Hide, all you little ones ♪

21:40.208 --> 21:41.958
♪ Rush now ♪

21:42.041 --> 21:45.250
♪ Into the middle of nowhere ♪

21:45.333 --> 21:47.916
♪ Singing and laughter will die ♪

21:48.000 --> 21:50.708
-Oh, look at my face!
-[laughs]

21:50.791 --> 21:57.333
♪ Dreamless sleep
Follows the Nowhere King ♪

21:57.416 --> 22:01.416
♪ When his kingdom comes
Darkness is nigh ♪

22:01.500 --> 22:03.666
I think I know this song.

22:04.750 --> 22:06.833
♪ Quiet ♪

22:06.916 --> 22:08.625
♪ Crawl to the in-between ♪

22:08.708 --> 22:12.041
♪ Silent, secretive feeling ♪

22:12.125 --> 22:17.916
♪ Of fearsome hatred
That reaches the skies ♪

22:19.708 --> 22:26.333
♪ You will bring joy to the Nowhere King ♪

22:26.416 --> 22:33.416
♪ When he sees the light
Leaving your eyes ♪

22:40.875 --> 22:42.875
[closing theme music playing]

23:12.375 --> 23:14.583
[Horse galloping]

23:14.666 --> 23:16.666
[neighing]

23:17.333 --> 23:19.333
[whimsical music playing]
